author: ABC Radio National
title: Justin Trudeau elected next prime minister of Canada
text:
Wednesday 21 October 2015 8:24AM (view full episode) 
Canada's Prime Minister elect — Liberal Justin Trudeau — has addressed supporters at a victory rally in the nation's capital, Ottawa. 
The Liberals won 184 seats — 14 more than they needed to form a majority and oust Conservative Prime Minister Stephen Harper. 
Forty-three year old Trudeau becomes Canada's second-youngest ever leader, and now has the job of picking a Cabinet. 
Speaking at the Liberal party's victory rally, he promised a new beginning in Canadian politics.
